timeline.bodyText:
I think this was talked in the demo couple of weeks ago but thetoString() is probably too much here. I think that the end user is only interested in the field name and the reason why the value was rejected. So maybe just add those (field and codes) to the metadata in a way that the frontend can parse and map them to the corresponding field easily. Something like this maybe (?):
{
    "status": 400,
    "error": {
        "code": "validation_failure",
        "metadata": [
            "client.memberCode: NoColons, NoForwardslashes", 
            "client.subsystemCode: NoColons"
        ]
    }
}
Or there could be a totally different response object when validation failure happens
{
    "status": 400,
    "error": {
        "code": "validation_failure",
        "validation_errors": {
            "client.memberCode": [ 
               "NoColons", 
               "NoForwardslashes"
            ], 
            "client.subsystemCode": [
              "NoColons"
            ]
        }
    }
}
IDK probably needs some brainstorming between frontend and backend devs 🤔
